## Shifting Labels

Given a sequence of token ids, x= [t0, t1, t2, t3, t4] a model should learn that given t0, t1 predict t2. 

→ logits comes out of the model as (batch, seq_len, vocab_size) which is a full probability distribution over the vocabulary for every sequence in batch.

→ labels is (batch, seq_len) or integer token ids. 

However, F.cross_entropy expects specific shape contract of logits as (N, C) and labels as (N,) and requires a flattened list. Therefore you must collapse batch and sequence length together into one dimension. 

```python
def reshape_crossentropy(logits, labels):
	batch, seq_len, vocab_size = logits.shape
	logits = logits.view(batch * seq_len, vocab_size)
	labels = labels.view(batch * seq_len)
	return F.crossentropy(logits, labels)
```

